column5: I got a neighbour that's got a leaf blower that sounds like a F-18, love to do that to his. 6 leaves fall on his drive and he fires the damned thing up
I bet you got a great deal on that piece of crap. I haad one as well but didnt have the press to repair it properly.
What was inside? Did you fix it?

Must be a close relative of my neighbor!! Leaves??? I've heard the blower going all summer!! Wouldn't want any grass clippings on the grass, I guess, or have to bend a bit to sweep them with a broom!!!!
I get what your saying 100%.  But If I dumped $500 bucks in to a leaf blower, I'd be using that dang thing for EVERYTHING!  Get my moneys worth out of it.
When you wash your truck, the leaf blower would be great for removing the water and would certainly save getting the chamois all wet.
OUCH that hurt , have not laughed that hard in a long long time ...
I was a little PRESSED for time  so I had to hurry up !!!
Ahem......did you know there was a red switch you had to turn on first before you pulled the cord........ Awesome destruction ! Hmmm.. or are you collecting precious metals....lol
can you say, anger management  lol
Well there's yer problem - the fluidframistorquekadoozler was misaligned with the holycrappissingmeoffer!  Michael
And what did you learn about the insides
I hate when you take something apart to fix it and cant find the problem
What ever turns your "crank" !
note to self.  Never lend Whitespinnerbait anything!
Looks like the flux capacitor is screwed better get that checked.LOL!!
that's exactly what I'd like to do with  my neighbors leafblower that's been going all summer with clippings etc.. OCD can be such a terrible affliction---I should be a bit more understanding.
Jiminy Cricket man !!!!!!!!!!!!! Did you at least call the customer assistance number in the first pic??  I had a toaster like that once

A quick compresson test could have showed you that your machine was suffering from a cracked piston. You can order a new high compression piston online that'll guarantee that your machine will blow the weeds out of any whippper snipper on the market......
did you know the 3rd picture is outta focus????might be something wrong with your camera
nice...lol
I have exactly the same one! I could have used it for parts! Wait until BIg Cliff checks in, to use in real trouble
Classic!
I think you should back off the settings of your impact wrench a tad.....
I keep coming back and looking at these pics.Just AWESOME !!!! You didnt take a Vid did you That would keep me amused for hours !!!!
lol  Have you ever wondered what the inside of your camera looks like?
E
LOLOLOL
Good idea to take pictures when you're taking it "apart" It will be a breeze to put it back together now....LOL

I feel like doing the same thing with my weed eater.  Likely just needs a carb tune up...But I like your idea beter!
